# Conventional Commit Message Template
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Types:
#   feat:     A new feature
#   fix:      A bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation only changes
#   style:    Changes that don't affect code meaning (white-space, formatting)
#   refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf:     Code change that improves performance
#   test:     Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
#   build:    Changes to build system or external dependencies
#   ci:       Changes to CI configuration files and scripts
#   chore:    Other changes that don't modify src or test files
#
# Scope (optional):
#   theme, headless, api, docs, config, deps
#
# Example:
#   feat(headless): add product search functionality
#   fix(theme): resolve cart quantity update bug
#   docs: update README with deployment instructions
#
# Breaking Changes:
#   Add "BREAKING CHANGE:" in the body for breaking changes
#
# Reference Issues:
#   Closes #123, Fixes #456, Refs #789
